OL,6,FJanine McKinney, Chief Crown
OL,7,FProsecutor for CPS East Midlands,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Today, Emad Kaky has faced the
OL,9,Fconsequences of his actions in trying
OL,10,Fto get a young, innocent girl
OL,11,Fsubjected to female genital mutilation
OL,12,Fand to be forced into a marriage not
OL,13,Fof her choosing.
OL,15,F"Had he succeeded in his plans, this
OL,16,Fchild would have suffered unimaginable
OL,17,Fphysical and mental harm.
OL,19,F"During the trial, we presented
OL,20,Fevidence that the defendant considered
OL,21,Fthis behaviour to be normal.
